message.content:
1. Kinematic parameters were measured before and after the 3-week training in RWM.
2. The stride length increased by 4.54% after the 3-week training in RWM.
3. The increase in stride length was statistically significant with a p-value of less than 0.0001.
4. The contact time increased by 4.58% after the 3-week training in RWM.
5. The increase in contact time was statistically significant with a p-value of less than 0.001.
6. The stride frequency decreased by 4.44% after the 3-week training in RWM.
7. The decrease in stride frequency was statistically significant with a p-value of less than 0.0001.
8. The internal work decreased by 7.09% after the 3-week training in RWM.
9. The decrease in internal work was statistically significant with a p-value of less than 0.05.

messages.content:
Statement: Kinematic parameters measured before and after the 3-week training in RWM showed increased stride length (4.54%; p<0.0001) and contact time (4.58%; p<0.001); inversely, a decreased stride frequency (4.44%; p<0.0001) and internal work (7.09%; p<0.05) were found.
